## EMAIL STRUCTURE

The email is composed and passed to send_alert_email as HTML.
Follow this structure exactly — no additions, no reordering.

### HEADER BLOCK
  <h2> Lyric Application — Patch Validation Summary </h2>
  <p>  Generated: <date time> | Patch Window End: <Day HH:MM>  </p>
  <p>  Please review the servers below and take action where needed.  </p>
  <hr/>

### SECTION 1 — SERVERS UNREACHABLE
  Only include if unreachable list is non-empty.

  Heading (amber #b45309, bold, 16px):
    "Servers Unreachable"

  Message line:
    "We were unable to connect to the following servers.
     Please look into this."

  Table columns:
    Server Name | Patch Window | Reboot Required

  One row per server from unreachable list.

### SECTION 2 — REBOOT NOT CONFIRMED
  Only include if failed list is non-empty.

  Heading (red #b91c1c, bold, 16px):
    "Reboot Not Confirmed Within Patch Window"

  Message line:
    "Could you please check if these servers were rebooted
     during the patch window?"

  Table columns:
    Server Name | Patch Window | Boot Time | Reboot Required

  One row per server from failed list.
  Boot Time format: DD-Mon-YYYY HH:MM  (e.g. 13-Mar-2026 07:45)
  If boot time is null or N/A: show "Not recorded"

### SECTION 3 — VALIDATION PENDING
  Only include if pending list is non-empty.

  Heading (blue #1d4ed8, bold, 16px):
    "Validation Pending"

  Message line:
    "Could you please provide an update on the patching status
     for the following servers?"

  Table columns:
    Server Name | Patch Window | Reboot Required

  One row per server from pending list.

### FOOTER BLOCK
  <hr/>
  <p style="font-size:12px; color:#6b7280; font-style:italic;">
    Enterprise Patch Intelligence System — Automated Alert
  </p>

