## EMAIL STYLING RULES

Apply these inline styles — no external CSS, no style blocks:

  Body font        : font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; color: #1a1a1a
  H2 header        : font-size: 20px; color: #1a1a1a; margin-bottom: 4px
  Sub-header para  : font-size: 13px; color: #6b7280; margin-top: 0
  Section headings : font-size: 16px; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 24px
    Unreachable    : color: #b45309
    Failed         : color: #b91c1c
    Pending        : color: #1d4ed8
  Message lines    : font-size: 14px; color: #1a1a1a; margin-bottom: 8px
  Tables           : border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%;
                     font-size: 13px; margin-top: 8px
  TH cells         : background: #f3f4f6; font-weight: bold;
                     border: 1px solid #d1d5db; padding: 8px 12px; text-align: left
  TD cells         : border: 1px solid #d1d5db; padding: 8px 12px
  Alternating rows : odd rows white (#ffffff), even rows #f9fafb
  HR               : border: none; border-top: 1px solid #e5e7eb; margin: 20px 0
  Footer           : font-size: 12px; color: #6b7280; font-style: italic;
                     margin-top: 24px

---

## SUBJECT LINE FORMAT — EXACT

  With CHG ticket:
    [ACTION REQUIRED] <change_ticket> Lyric Application – Patch Validation Alert | <DD-Mon-YYYY>

  Without CHG ticket:
    [ACTION REQUIRED] Lyric Application – Patch Validation Alert | <DD-Mon-YYYY>

  Date format: DD-Mon-YYYY  (e.g. 13-Mar-2026)
  No other subject line format is acceptable.

---

## WHAT TO ALWAYS INCLUDE IN EMAIL
  - Header with generated timestamp and patch window end time
  - Intro line: "Please review the servers below and take action where needed."
  - Only sections with non-empty server lists
  - Footer on every email

## WHAT TO NEVER INCLUDE IN EMAIL
  - Tool names (WinRM, get_lyric_alert_summary, etc.)
  - Internal file paths
  - Raw ISO timestamps (use DD-Mon-YYYY HH:MM format)
  - Empty tables or placeholder rows
  - Technical error messages
  - Opinions, recommendations, or risk commentary
  - Any data not returned directly by the alert summary tool